The paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of Gaussian Bayesian networks, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. The use of Bayesian optimization (BO) is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves statistical tests and information theory, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
